A SUSPECT (45) was arrested on charges of murder, armed robbery, possession of an unlicensed firearm with ammunition as well as pointing of a firearm. The man was arrested on 26 December in Mkhuhlu near Bushbuckridge on allegations that he shot Aby Nginindza (40) on that day at a tavern in Mkhuhlu. Police spokesman Brigadier Selvy Mohlala said members of the police at Calcutta received information regarding a shooting incident at the said premises. Upon arrival at the scene, they found the victim lying on the ground with a gunshot wound to the head but he was still alive. He was certified dead on arrival at a hospital. You must be SIGNED IN to read comments  After the suspect was traced and arrested, police also discovered that the man allegedly committed an armed robbery, where cash was taken from a male victim. It is said that this happened moments after the shooting. The suspect appeared in the Mkhuhlu Magistrates Court and the case was postponed to 6 January. .